American Andy Roddick Pulls Out of French Open With Right Shoulder Injury

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-05-19T20:15:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/american-andy-roddick-pulls-out-of-french-open-with-right-shoulder-injury.html
American  Andy Roddick  pulled out of
the French Open today with a right shoulder injury, four days
before the start of the clay-court Grand Slam tennis tournament.  Roddick, who is ranked 11th in the world, pulled out of the
doubles final at the Italian Open last weekend and had been
considered questionable for the French Open.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  